{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Quantum-resistant strategies in the realm of Blockchain are starting to emerge.",
    "For instance, Kiktenko et al. [74] introduced a Blockchain platform designed to be quantum-safe, relying on information-theoretically secure authentication through a quantum key distributed via an urban fiber network.",
    "In a more recent development, Rajan and Visser [75] introduced a concept of a quantum networked time machine, where the Blockchain is encoded into a non-simultaneously coexisting photon state known as a secular Greenberger-Horne-Zeilinger state.",
    "DiscussionIn this systematic review, we explored the literature relating to the implementation of blockchain technology in the field of the sports industry, using the search strategy in section 2.",
    "We were able to extract 38 papers from 2018 until 2023."
  ],
